label: CX

components.name: ID Number
components.comment: The ID Number must uniquely identify the associated object, i.e., any object with which the field is associated.  Note - despite the component being named “ID Number” this component is an ST string data type, not numeric, so the component is not limited to just numbers

components.name: Assigning Authority
components.comment: The assigning authority is a unique name for the system (or organization, agency or department) that created the ID number in Sequence 1 (CX.1).

components.name: Identifier Type Code
components.comment: The value provides indicates the type for the identifier.  HL7 has provided a list of suggested values.

name: CX
